We need to look at the transactions that “injected” money into the business through paid‐in capital. In our case these are the rows whose id begins with “Initial20231231001” and which record a “Cash deposit”, “Bank deposit” and “Fixed Assets”. Their amounts are:

• Cash deposit: 5,000,000.0  
• Bank deposit: 15,000,000.0  
• Fixed Assets: 8,000,000.0  

Adding these amounts we get:  
5,000,000.0 + 15,000,000.0 + 8,000,000.0 = 28,000,000.0

Since there are no later transactions that increase or decrease the paid-in capital amount (only other transactions such as purchases, expenses, sales, etc.), the final paid-in capital remains the same as the initial injection.

Thus, the paid-in capital initial and end value is 28,000,000.00 each.

Below is the answer in the required json format:

{
  "solution": {
    "Paid-in Capital Initial Value": "28000000.00",
    "Paid-in Capital End Value": "28000000.00"
  }
}
